This paper deals with a machine learning problem of learning with label proportions, which is a common problem in many sub-fields of computer science such as natural language processing, computer vision, and data science. The proposed method, $\propto$SVM, is a new approach that models the latent unknown instance labels together with the known group label proportions in a large-margin framework. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data science (cs.DS). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely sub-category as the paper proposes a new machine learning method.
